@page "/"

<h3>Async BasicSample — Blazor Web App</h3>
<p>
    This app mirrors the four API proposal scenarios from <strong>dotnet/runtime#128096</strong>
    using the manual Blazor form pattern.
</p>
<p>
    Each page calls <code>Validator.TryValidateObjectAsync</code> on submit and copies the results
    into a <code>ValidationMessageStore</code> so Blazor's built-in validation UI stays in sync.
</p>

<div class="list-group">
    <a href="/scenario1" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 1:</strong> <code>User</code> with <code>[IsValidName]</code> and <code>[UsernameAvailableAsync]</code>
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario2" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 2:</strong> <code>Order</code> with <code>IValidatableObject</code> and <code>[AsyncProductExists]</code>
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario3" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 3:</strong> <code>MoneyTransfer</code> with <code>IAsyncValidatableObject</code>
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario4" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 4:</strong> <code>Event</code> with <code>[AsyncDateRangeValid]</code>
    </a>
</div>
